This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of one-stage object detectors, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed RoIConv operator and AlignDet architecture involve deep learning techniques and optimization, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the misalignment issue in object detection, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the COCO dataset is used for evaluation, which is a popular benchmark in multimedia (cs.MM).
